// some useful adb commands (please add to this list)

// start and stop the eft service
adb -d shell am force-stop eft.com.launcher
adb -d shell am startservice eft.com.launcher/com.linkly.launcher.service.POSitiveSvc

// keyboard and font related tricks
pax_adb.exe shell ime disable com.google.android.inputmethod.pinyin/.PinyinIME
pax_adb.exe shell ime disable com.android.inputmethod.latin/.LatinIME
pax_adb.exe shell ime disable jp.co.omronsoft.openwnn/.OpenWnnJAJP
pax_adb.exe shell ime enable eft.com.poskeyboard/.PosIME


// shell access
pax_adb.exe shell  //Grants Shell Access
pax_adb.exe -d backup -apk -noshared -all -f A920.bk
pax_adb.exe restore A920.bk


// Useful commands to pull database from Android
adb.exe pull  /data/data/eft.com.apay/databases
adb.exe push databases/CashiersDB3  /data/data/eft.com.apay/shared_prefs
adb.exe push cfg  /data/data/eft.com.apay/files



adb shell pm uninstall -k com.pax.ipp.neptune
          pm uninstall -k eft.com.launcher


dpm set-device-owner eft.com.apay/eft.com.amal.ui.UIKiosk


Crash Reporting
APay uses Crashlytics for runtime crash reporting, if you want adding to the reporting emails contact jim
https://fabric.io/kits/android/crashlytics


Online Testing Service:

Google Provide an excellent automated test tool: firebase.google.com
This will run through all possible execution paths based on User Input and if configured correctly can excerise all aspects of the APP (Excluding EMV and Cardbased)


Database Export & Examination
It is possible on Dev Devices to download the entire Database for APay and View and Edit it on your PC:
To pull the database use the following command:  adb.exe pull  /data/data/eft.com.apay/databases
Once pulled use the DB Browser tool available from: https://sqlitebrowser.org/


/* build line */
gradlew --profile --recompile-scripts --rerun-tasks assembleDebug



